{{Quote|If you break anything the septa will have my head.|Vayon Poole ordering two Stark servants|The Pointy End}}

'''Vayon Poole''' is a minor character in the [[Season 1|first season]]. He is played by [[Matthew Scurfield]]. He was first mentioned in &quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot; and only appears in &quot;[[The Pointy End]].&quot; Poole serves [[House Stark]] as the Steward of [[Winterfell]].

sections.Biography:
===Background===
[[File:Jeyne Poole.jpg|thumb|150px|right|Vayon's daughter, Jeyne]]
Vayon Poole serves [[House Stark]] as the Steward of [[Winterfell]]. He is the father ofÂ five daughters, one of whom, [[Jeyne Poole]], is [[Sansa Stark]]'s friend.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 1]]===
When Maester [[Luwin]] approaches [[Catelyn Stark]] to talk about the costs of the royal visit to Winterfell the need to replace the members of the household that accompanied Lord [[Eddard Stark|Eddard]] to [[King's Landing]], she, grieving for her son, tells Luwin to have Poole see to the task. Luwin notes that Poole also went south with Lord Stark.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Poole is later killed by Lannister men during the [[Massacre in the Red Keep|purge of the Stark household]] ordered by King [[Joffrey]] after Lord Stark tries to remove him from the [[Iron Throne|throne]]. He dies while he and his men are packing for an evacuation Ned had ordered in anticipation of his move against Joffrey.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
